## Kubernetes as a Distributed OS

- Kubernetes provides core OS functions, but for a distributed\
cluster of machines.
- It abstracts infrastructure, creating a unified platform for applications.

| Operating System Function | Kubernetes Equivalent                        |
|---------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Hardware Abstraction      | Abstracts nodes into a single compute pool   |
| Resource Management       | Manages CPU/memory with requests & limits    |
| Process Management        | Manages container lifecycle (like processes) |
| Networking                | Provides cluster-wide pod networking         |
| Storage Management        | Orchestrates persistent data with PVs/PVCs   |
| Security & Isolation      | Isolates workloads via namespaces/policies   |

