## History of Linux


- **1991**: Linux created by Linus Torvalds as a free,\
open-source kernel, starting its path to\
server adoption
- **1992**: Kernel released publicly, enabling global\
collaboration and server-focused development
- **2001**: Linux server shipments grew 15% annually,\
showing rising enterprise trust
- **2004**: Powered ~50% of global server blade\
units, marking data center dominance
- **2025**: Runs on 78.3% of web-facing servers\
worldwide, reflecting broad, vendor-independent\
acceptance

![image](/images/datacenter.png){x=1065 y=400 h=550 cx=1150 cy=400}

